name: 5/8" Amber on Wood Eyelets
description:
A stunning amber cabachon within a thin silver bezel, set on a 5/8" Catalox wood eyelet.

The amber used by Quetzalli Jewelry comes from Chiapas, Mexico and it is approximately 22 million to 26 million years of age. Chiapas Amber is considered a precious material, highly valued due to its protective and magical properties in addition to the fact that it is quite difficult to be mined.

Sold as a pair.
